Interface DsaHeap<ElemType>

Type Parameters:
ElemType - the type of elements held in this heap. The elements must either:
  • Implement the Comparable interface to define a natural ordering, or
  • Be compatible with a custom Comparator provided by the implementation.
All Superinterfaces:
DsaTree<ElemType>
All Known Implementing Classes:
DsaMaxHeap, DsaMinHeap
public interface DsaHeap<ElemType> extends DsaTree<ElemType>
A generic interface for implementing a Heap data structure.

  • Method Details

    • insert

      void insert(ElemType element)
      Inserts the specified element into the heap. Postconditions:
      • The element is added to the heap, maintaining the heap invariant.
      • DsaTree.size() increases by one.
      Specified by:
      insert in interface DsaTree<ElemType>
      Parameters:
      element - the element to be inserted into the heap
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if the specified element is null

    • extract

      ElemType extract()
      Extracts and returns the top element from the heap. -- Largest element for max-heap -- Smallest element for min-heap The top element is the root of the heap and is removed from the heap, maintaining the heap invariant.
      Returns:
      the extracted top element
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the heap is empty

    • peek

      ElemType peek()
      Returns, but does not remove, the top (min or max) element of the heap.
      Returns:
      the top element of the heap
      Throws:
      IllegalStateException - if the heap is empty
